The paper deals with the optimality of network coding in packet networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The use of memory in network coding protocols suggests that the paper may be related to information theory (cs.IT) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The focus on convergence and stopping times suggests that the paper may also be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) or systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the use of probabilistic analysis suggests that the paper may also be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
